howAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=857.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> continuing</span><hr size=1> That's easy you idiot.  I was saving your as--&quot;<br>
Just then the other two gunmen appeard from behind the shop and shot at the figure.  Soon after, the figure crumpled down holding it's gut.  <br>
   Sid aimed his gun and fired.  He fired until there was no doubt that the other two were dead.  Then he noticed his arm.  Bleeding on the one side, and a tear in his big coat, a bullet had glanced it.  He grimiced and continued on to the figure. <br>
   &quot;Who the hell...&quot; He muttered, taking of it's hood... Sid almost jumped back.  &quot;Aw damn...&quot;<br>
   &quot;I tried...to warn you... Leo's on the run... he's got every hired...ugh...gun on your ass.... you better get outta town...before...&quot;  Gasped Roxy with her last dying breath.<br>
   Sid closed his eyes for a second, and for the first time in a while he almost felt sad.  Closing her open eyes with his rough hand he muttered, &quot;Don't worry lady... I never gave up on a job yet... and I sure as hell don't intend to now...&quot;<br>
   He drug her body into a nearby dumpster.  Not much of funeral, but given that it was Grunge City, it really didn't matter.  Sid got up and made his way to Leo's house.<br>
   When he got to the large building, he check the door.  Locked.  Sid pulled out his handgun and blew off the lock.  Not too many people noticed, and those who did figured that if he was messin' with Leo, he probably was going to never shoot anything else again.<br>
   Walking into the messy building, Sid noticed a noise in the back.  Walking over drawers that were out, and papers that were still flying in the air, he got into some kind of back room.  In it, was an old TV hooked up to a VCR.  Static was playing, and attached to a video tape, a note said, &quot;Play me&quot;.  <br>
   Sid put the tape in, and sat back.  Leo's terrifying mug came into view.  &quot;Sid!  Hello my good friend.  Turns out that you never miss a solid dish in your life.  That card of that chick Roxy?  Pretty good deal I tell ya what.  Her real name's actually Roxane Summers, but given her line of work, I don't think it made a difference.  44 years old.  Can you believe it?  She don't look a day over 24.  But that's what happens when you know a good plastic surgeon.<br>
   &quot;She's got the money Sid.  Even if she was a no good whore, she still was good at getting the fat cows to hire her... So, the credibility issue isn't and issue anymore.  You dig?&quot;  The camera panned to three men, all with guns, axes, and knives.  &quot;These guy?  These are my guys that make sure Roxy can't ever withdraw her money again, if you know what I mean.  But if you do get a message from her, or if you come in a couple days to see if I'm still around...<br>
   Well, I'm not.  You're a detective, detect!  Although it's going to be kind of hard when you have all my wolves, lions, and sharks on ya.<br>
   I'm not afraid of you Sid.  You're old.  You're out of touch.  I got your reality check right here buddy.&quot;  Leo said waving a gun about.  &quot;Right here... but I want to see if you can find me first...  It's going to be a tricky one it is.  After all, when you're the devil, you got plenty of places to hide, and best of all, you got plenty of goons to do your dirty work.&quot;  He held up a blinking light.  &quot;See this?  This is what I can my 'insurance'.  It's a homing beacon telling whatever sharks, lions, wolves, or even rats that I've hired to come and kill you.  And believe me.  It's started.  It's on the back of the VCR, and I had to talk enough to give 'em a chance to get ya...&quot;  <br>
   Leo took out a cigar.  &quot;You got real issues Sid.  Maybe you should work'em out... but given the situation, the only doctor you'll be see'in is the mortition...&quot;  He cackled with laughter... &quot;See ya around...&quot;<br>
  Sid picked up his gun from the endtable.  Things were going to get a whole lot worse real quick.  He turned around to the sound on cocking guns, to see three men and two women with semi-automatic weapons pointed straight out of him.<br>
   No way he was going to get out of this one... No one could save him now...<br>
